Consciousness without feature without end luminous all around is not experienced through the solidity of earth the liquidity of water the radiance of fire the windiness of wind the divinity of devas the allness of the All

Freed dissociated  released from ten things Bāhuna the Tathāgata dwells with unrestricted awareness
Which ten
